genresAdvancedInfo.name: swedish grindcore
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Swedish grindcore is a subgenre of extreme metal that originated in Sweden in the late 1980s. It is characterized by its fast and aggressive sound, with short songs that often feature blast beats and growled vocals. The lyrics often deal with political and social issues, as well as themes of violence and gore. Swedish grindcore has a dedicated fanbase and has produced several influential bands, including Nasum and Rotten Sound.
